-- Everbright Bank May Raise 20 Billion Yuan in IPO, Century Weekly Reports
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-26T05:09:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-26/everbright-bank-may-raise-20-billion-yuan-in-ipo-century-weekly-reports.html

          
          
             China Everbright Bank Co. may raise
20 billion yuan ($2.95 billion) in an initial public offering of
yuan-denominated shares in China, Century Weekly magazine
reported in its latest issue, citing unidentified people at the
bank.  
 The bank would prepare to sell shares publicly in Hong Kong
soon after its IPO in China, the magazine reported.  
